Bug 2021848 - Show calendar event URL in dialog regardless of protocol handler. r=mkmelin

Bug 1706158 removed the user toggle for the related link and updated the
summary pane to always show the URL if present. However, it left behind
strict protocol validation logic (showOrHideItemURL) in the event edit dialog.

This caused a UI inconsistency where links with unregistered protocols
(e.g., custom or app-specific schemes) were visible in the read-only summary
pane but completely hidden when editing the event. This gave the false
impression of data loss and prevented users from copying the link.

This patch removes the OS protocol handler checks from calendar-dialog-utils.js
and calendar-item-iframe.js. The URL field will now consistently display
based solely on the presence of the string, matching the summary pane's behavior.

Inspired by https://github.com/Betterbird/thunderbird-patches/blob/main/140/bugs/NNN33-always-show-calendar-item-links.patch

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D286637

